a000001.name: Number of groups of order n.

a000002.name: Kolakoski sequence: a(n) is length of n-th run; a(1) = 1; sequence consists just of 1's and 2's.

a000006.name: Integer part of square root of n-th prime.

a000008.name: Number of ways of making change for n cents using coins of 1, 2, 5, 10 cents.

a000009.name: Expansion of Product_{m >= 1} (1 + x^m); number of partitions of n into distinct parts; number of partitions of n into odd parts.

a000010.name: Euler totient function phi(n): count numbers <= n and prime to n.

a000011.name: Number of n-bead necklaces (turning over is allowed) where complements are equivalent.

a000012.name: The simplest sequence of positive numbers: the all 1's sequence.

a000013.name: Definition (1): Number of n-bead binary necklaces with beads of 2 colors where the colors may be swapped but turning over is not allowed.

a000014.name: Number of series-reduced trees with n nodes.

a000016.name: a(n) is the number of distinct (infinite) output sequences from binary n-stage shift register which feeds back the complement of the last stage.

a000025.name: Coefficients of the 3rd order mock theta function f(q).

a000026.name: Mosaic numbers or multiplicative projection of n: if n = Product (p_j^k_j) then a(n) = Product (p_j * k_j).

a000027.name: The positive integers. Also called the natural numbers, the whole numbers or the counting numbers, but these terms are ambiguous.

a000029.name: Number of necklaces with n beads of 2 colors, allowing turning over (these are also called bracelets).

a000031.name: Number of n-bead necklaces with 2 colors when turning over is not allowed; also number of output sequences from a simple n-stage cycling shift register; also number of binary irreducible polynomials whose degree divides n.

a000035.name: Period 2: repeat [0, 1]; a(n) = n mod 2; parity of n.

a000036.name: Let A(n) = #{(i,j): i^2 + j^2 <= n}, V(n) = Pi*n, P(n) = A(n) - V(n); A000099 gives values of n where |P(n)| sets a new record; sequence gives closest integer to P(A000099(n)).

a000037.name: Numbers that are not squares (or, the nonsquares).

a000039.name: Coefficient of q^(2n) in the series expansion of Ramanujan's mock theta function f(q).

a000043.name: Mersenne exponents: primes p such that 2^p - 1 is prime. Then 2^p - 1 is called a Mersenne prime.

a000044.name: Dying rabbits: a(0) = 1; for 1 <= n <= 12, a(n) = Fibonacci(n); for n >= 13, a(n) = a(n-1) + a(n-2) - a(n-13).

a000046.name: Number of primitive n-bead necklaces (turning over is allowed) where complements are equivalent.

a000048.name: Number of n-bead necklaces with beads of 2 colors and primitive period n, when turning over is not allowed but the two colors can be interchanged.

a000055.name: Number of trees with n unlabeled nodes.

a000058.name: Sylvester's sequence: a(n+1) = a(n)^2 - a(n) + 1, with a(0) = 2.

a000059.name: Numbers k such that (2k)^4 + 1 is prime.

a000060.name: Number of signed trees with n nodes.

a000064.name: Partial sums of (unordered) ways of making change for n cents using coins of 1, 2, 5, 10 cents.

a000066.name: Smallest number of vertices in trivalent graph with girth (shortest cycle) = n.

a000069.name: Odious numbers: numbers with an odd number of 1's in their binary expansion.

a000070.name: a(n) = Sum_{k=0..n} p(k) where p(k) = number of partitions of k (A000041).

a000073.name: Tribonacci numbers: a(n) = a(n-1) + a(n-2) + a(n-3) for n >= 3 with a(0) = a(1) = 0 and a(2) = 1.

a000078.name: Tetranacci numbers: a(n) = a(n-1) + a(n-2) + a(n-3) + a(n-4) for n >= 4 with a(0) = a(1) = a(2) = 0 and a(3) = 1.

a000081.name: Number of unlabeled rooted trees with n nodes (or connected functions with a fixed point).

a000083.name: Number of mixed Husimi trees with n nodes; or polygonal cacti with bridges.

a000084.name: Number of series-parallel networks with n unlabeled edges. Also called yoke-chains by Cayley and MacMahon.

a000085.name: Number of self-inverse permutations on n letters, also known as involutions; number of standard Young tableaux with n cells.

a000086.name: Number of solutions to x^2 - x + 1 == 0 (mod n).

a000087.name: Number of unrooted nonseparable planar maps with n edges and a distinguished face.

a000088.name: Number of graphs on n unlabeled nodes.

a000089.name: Number of solutions to x^2 + 1 == 0 (mod n).

a000095.name: Number of fixed points of GAMMA_0 (n) of type i.

a000097.name: Number of partitions of n if there are two kinds of 1's and two kinds of 2's.

a000098.name: Number of partitions of n if there are two kinds of 1, two kinds of 2 and two kinds of 3.

a000100.name: a(n) is the number of compositions of n in which the maximal part is 3.

a000101.name: Record gaps between primes (upper end) (compare A002386, which gives lower ends of these gaps).

a000102.name: a(n) = number of compositions of n in which the maximum part size is 4.

a000104.name: Number of n-celled free polyominoes without holes.

a000105.name: Number of free polyominoes (or square animals) with n cells.

a000106.name: 2nd power of rooted tree enumerator; number of linear forests of 2 rooted trees.

a000107.name: Number of rooted trees with n nodes and a single labeled node; pointed rooted trees; vertebrates.

a000109.name: Number of simplicial polyhedra with n nodes; simple planar graphs with 3n-6 edges; maximal simple planar graphs; 3-connected planar triangulations; 3-connected triangulations of the sphere; 3-connected cubic planar graphs.

a000111.name: Euler or up/down numbers: e.g.f. sec(x) + tan(x). Also for n >= 2, half the number of alternating permutations on n letters (A001250).

a000113.name: Number of transformation groups of order n.

a000114.name: Number of cusps of principal congruence subgroup GAMMA^{hat}(n).

a000116.name: Number of even sequences with period 2n (bisection of A000013).

a000117.name: Number of even sequences with period 2n (bisection of A000011).

a000118.name: Number of ways of writing n as a sum of 4 squares; also theta series of four-dimensional cubic lattice Z^4.

a000119.name: Number of representations of n as a sum of distinct Fibonacci numbers.

a000120.name: 1's-counting sequence: number of 1's in binary expansion of n (or the binary weight of n).

a000121.name: Number of representations of n as a sum of Fibonacci numbers (1 is allowed twice as a part).

a000122.name: Expansion of Jacobi theta function theta_3(x) = Sum_{m =-oo..oo} x^(m^2) (number of integer solutions to k^2 = n).

a000123.name: Number of binary partitions: number of partitions of 2n into powers of 2.

a000124.name: Central polygonal numbers (the Lazy Caterer's sequence): n(n+1)/2 + 1; or, maximal number of pieces formed when slicing a pancake with n cuts.

a000125.name: Cake numbers: maximal number of pieces resulting from n planar cuts through a cube (or cake): C(n+1,3) + n + 1.

a000127.name: Maximal number of regions obtained by joining n points around a circle by straight lines. Also number of regions in 4-space formed by n-1 hyperplanes.

a000130.name: One-half the number of permutations of length n with exactly 1 rising or falling successions.

a000131.name: Number of asymmetrical dissections of n-gon.

a000132.name: Number of ways of writing n as a sum of 5 squares.

a000133.name: Number of Boolean functions of n variables.

a000134.name: Positive zeros of Bessel function of order 0 rounded to nearest integer.

a000136.name: Number of ways of folding a strip of n labeled stamps.

a000140.name: Kendall-Mann numbers: the maximal number of inversions in a permutation on n letters is floor(n*(n-1)/4); a(n) is the number of permutations with this many inversions.

a000141.name: Number of ways of writing n as a sum of 6 squares.

a000143.name: Number of ways of writing n as a sum of 8 squares.

a000144.name: Number of ways of writing n as a sum of 10 squares.

a000145.name: Number of ways of writing n as a sum of 12 squares.

a000150.name: Number of dissections of an n-gon, rooted at an exterior edge, asymmetric with respect to that edge.

a000151.name: Number of oriented rooted trees with n nodes. Also rooted trees with n nodes and 2-colored non-root nodes.

a000152.name: Number of ways of writing n as a sum of 16 squares.

a000156.name: Number of ways of writing n as a sum of 24 squares.

a000157.name: Number of Boolean functions of n variables.

a000161.name: Number of partitions of n into 2 squares.

a000162.name: Number of 3-dimensional polyominoes (or polycubes) with n cells.

a000164.name: Number of partitions of n into 3 squares (allowing part zero).

a000166.name: Subfactorial or rencontres numbers, or derangements: number of permutations of n elements with no fixed points.

a000169.name: Number of labeled rooted trees with n nodes: n^(n-1).

a000170.name: Number of ways of placing n nonattacking queens on an n X n board.

a000171.name: Number of self-complementary graphs with n nodes.

a000174.name: Number of partitions of n into 5 squares.

a000178.name: Superfactorials: product of first n factorials.

a000179.name: Ménage numbers: a(0) = 1, a(1) = -1, and for n >= 2, a(n) = number of permutations s of [0, ..., n-1] such that s(i) != i and s(i) != i+1 (mod n) for all i.

a000182.name: Tangent (or "Zag") numbers: e.g.f. tan(x), also (up to signs) e.g.f. tanh(x).

a000183.name: Number of discordant permutations of length n.

a000184.name: Number of genus 0 rooted maps with 3 faces with n vertices.

a000186.name: Number of 3 X n Latin rectangles in which the first row is in order.

a000188.name: (1) Number of solutions to x^2 == 0 (mod n). (2) Also square root of largest square dividing n. (3) Also max_{ d divides n } gcd(d, n/d).

a000189.name: Number of solutions to x^3 == 0 (mod n).

a000190.name: Number of solutions to x^4 == 0 (mod n).

a000194.name: n appears 2n times, for n >= 1; also nearest integer to square root of n.

a000196.name: Integer part of square root of n. Or, number of positive squares <= n. Or, n appears 2n+1 times.

a000198.name: Largest order of automorphism group of a tournament with n nodes.

a000199.name: Coefficient of q^(2n-1) in the series expansion of Ramanujan's mock theta function f(q).

a000201.name: Lower Wythoff sequence (a Beatty sequence): a(n) = floor(n*phi), where phi = (1+sqrt(5))/2 = A001622.

a000204.name: Lucas numbers (beginning with 1): L(n) = L(n-1) + L(n-2) with L(1) = 1, L(2) = 3.

a000207.name: Number of inequivalent ways of dissecting a regular (n+2)-gon into n triangles by n-1 non-intersecting diagonals under rotations and reflections; also the number of planar 2-trees.

a000208.name: Number of even sequences with period 2n.

a000213.name: Tribonacci numbers: a(n) = a(n-1) + a(n-2) + a(n-3) with a(0)=a(1)=a(2)=1.

a000216.name: Take sum of squares of digits of previous term, starting with 2.

a000218.name: Take sum of squares of digits of previous term; start with 3.

a000219.name: Number of planar partitions (or plane partitions) of n.

a000220.name: Number of asymmetric trees with n nodes (also called identity trees).

a000221.name: Take sum of squares of digits of previous term; start with 5.

a000223.name: Let A(n) = #{(i,j,k): i^2 + j^2 + k^2 <= n}, V(n) = (4/3)Pi*n^(3/2), P(n) = A(n) - V(n); A000092 gives values of n where |P(n)| sets a new record; sequence gives (nearest integer to, I believe) P(A000092(n)).

a000226.name: Number of n-node unlabeled connected graphs with one cycle of length 3.

a000230.name: a(0)=2; for n>=1, a(n) = smallest prime p such that there is a gap of exactly 2n between p and next prime, or -1 if no such prime exists.

a000231.name: Number of inequivalent Boolean functions of n variables under action of complementing group.

a000232.name: Construct a triangle as in A036262. Sequence is one less than the position of the first number larger than 2 in the n-th row (n-th difference).

a000235.name: Number of n-node rooted trees of height 3.

a000236.name: Maximum m such that there are no two adjacent elements belonging to the same n-th power residue class modulo some prime p in the sequence 1,2,...,m (equivalently, there is no n-th power residue modulo p in the sequence 1/2,2/3,...,(m-1)/m).

a000237.name: Number of mixed Husimi trees with n nodes; or rooted polygonal cacti with bridges.

a000238.name: Number of oriented trees with n nodes.

a000240.name: Rencontres numbers: number of permutations of [n] with exactly one fixed point.

a000241.name: Crossing number of complete graph with n nodes.

a000242.name: 3rd power of rooted tree enumerator; number of linear forests of 3 rooted trees.

a000243.name: Number of trees with n nodes, 2 of which are labeled.

a000246.name: Number of permutations in the symmetric group S_n that have odd order.

a000252.name: Number of invertible 2 X 2 matrices mod n.

a000254.name: Unsigned Stirling numbers of first kind, s(n+1,2): a(n+1) = (n+1)*a(n) + n!.

a000256.name: Number of simple triangulations of the plane with n nodes.

a000257.name: Number of rooted bicubic maps: a(n) = (8*n-4)*a(n-1)/(n+2) for n >= 2, a(0) = a(1) = 1.

a000259.name: Number of certain rooted planar maps.

a000260.name: Number of rooted simplicial 3-polytopes with n+3 nodes; or rooted 3-connected triangulations with 2n+2 faces; or rooted 3-connected trivalent maps with 2n+2 vertices.

a000262.name: Number of "sets of lists": number of partitions of {1,...,n} into any number of lists, where a list means an ordered subset.

a000264.name: Number of 3-edge-connected rooted cubic maps with 2n nodes and a distinguished Hamiltonian cycle.

a000265.name: Remove all factors of 2 from n; or largest odd divisor of n; or odd part of n.

a000267.name: Integer part of square root of 4n+1.

a000269.name: Number of trees with n nodes, 3 of which are labeled.

a000270.name: For n >= 2, a(n) = b(n+1)+b(n)+b(n-1), where the b(i) are the ménage numbers A000179; a(0)=a(1)=1.

a000272.name: Number of trees on n labeled nodes: n^(n-2) with a(0)=1.

a000273.name: Number of directed graphs (or digraphs) with n nodes.

a000274.name: Number of permutations of length n with 2 consecutive ascending pairs.

a000275.name: Coefficients of a Bessel function (reciprocal of J_0(z)); also pairs of permutations with rise/rise forbidden.

a000278.name: a(n) = a(n-1) + a(n-2)^2 for n >= 2 with a(0) = 0 and a(1) = 1.

a000279.name: Card matching: coefficients B[n,1] of t in the reduced hit polynomial A[n,n,n](t).

a000287.name: Number of rooted polyhedral graphs with n edges.

a000288.name: Tetranacci numbers: a(n) = a(n-1) + a(n-2) + a(n-3) + a(n-4) with a(0) = a(1) = a(2) = a(3) = 1.

a000289.name: A nonlinear recurrence: a(n) = a(n-1)^2 - 3*a(n-1) + 3 (for n>1).

a000291.name: Number of bipartite partitions of n white objects and 2 black ones.

a000295.name: Eulerian numbers (Euler's triangle: column k=2 of A008292, column k=1 of A173018).

a000296.name: Set partitions without singletons: number of partitions of an n-set into blocks of size > 1. Also number of cyclically spaced (or feasible) partitions.

a000299.name: Number of n-node rooted trees of height 4.

a000300.name: 4th power of rooted tree enumerator: linear forests of 4 rooted trees.

a000301.name: a(n) = a(n-1)*a(n-2) with a(0) = 1, a(1) = 2; also a(n) = 2^Fibonacci(n).

a000307.name: Number of 4-level labeled rooted trees with n leaves.

a000309.name: Number of rooted planar bridgeless cubic maps with 2n nodes.

a000311.name: Schroeder's fourth problem; also series-reduced rooted trees with n labeled leaves; also number of total partitions of n.

a000312.name: a(n) = n^n; number of labeled mappings from n points to themselves (endofunctions).

a000313.name: Number of permutations of length n with 3 consecutive ascending pairs.

a000314.name: Number of mixed Husimi trees with n nodes; or labeled polygonal cacti with bridges.

a000315.name: Number of reduced Latin squares of order n; also number of labeled loops (quasigroups with an identity element) with a fixed identity element.

a000316.name: Two decks each have n kinds of cards, 2 of each kind. The first deck is laid out in order. The second deck is shuffled and laid out next to the first. A match occurs if a card from the second deck is next to a card of the same kind from the first deck. a(n) is the number of ways of achieving no matches.

a000321.name: H_n(-1/2), where H_n(x) is Hermite polynomial of degree n.

a000324.name: A nonlinear recurrence: a(0) = 1, a(1) = 5, a(n) = a(n-1)^2 - 4*a(n-1) + 4 for n>1.

a000327.name: Number of partitions into non-integral powers.

a000328.name: Number of points of norm <= n^2 in square lattice.

a000341.name: Number of ways to pair up {1..2n} so sum of each pair is prime.

a000342.name: Number of n-node rooted trees of height 5.

a000343.name: 5th power of rooted tree enumerator; number of linear forests of 5 rooted trees.

a000348.name: Number of ways to pair up {1^2, 2^2, ..., (2n)^2 } so sum of each pair is prime.

a000349.name: One-half the number of permutations of length n with exactly 2 rising or falling successions.

a000352.name: One half of the number of permutations of [n] such that the differences have three runs with the same signs.

a000356.name: Number of rooted cubic maps with 2n nodes and a distinguished Hamiltonian cycle: (2n)!(2n+1)! / (n!^2*(n+1)!(n+2)!).

a000357.name: Number of 5-level labeled rooted trees with n leaves.

a000358.name: Number of binary necklaces of length n with no subsequence 00, excluding the necklace "0".

a000360.name: Distribution of nonempty triangles inside a fractal rep-4-tile.

a000363.name: Number of permutations of [n] with exactly 2 increasing runs of length at least 2.

a000365.name: Number of genus 0 rooted planar maps with 4 faces and n vertices.

a000366.name: Genocchi numbers of second kind (A005439) divided by 2^(n-1).

a000368.name: Number of connected graphs with one cycle of length 4.

a000369.name: Triangle of numbers related to triangle A049213; generalization of Stirling numbers of second kind A008277, Bessel triangle A001497.

a000370.name: Number of NPN-equivalence classes of Boolean functions of n or fewer variables.

a000372.name: Dedekind numbers or Dedekind's problem: number of monotone Boolean functions of n variables, number of antichains of subsets of an n-set, number of elements in a free distributive lattice on n generators, number of Sperner families.

a000374.name: Number of cycles (mod n) under doubling map.

a000377.name: Expansion of f(-q^3) * f(-q^8) * chi(-q^12) / chi(-q) in powers of q where chi(), f() are Ramanujan theta functions.

a000378.name: Sums of three squares: numbers of the form x^2 + y^2 + z^2.

a000380.name: Number of permutations of an n-sequence discordant with three given permutations (see reference) in n-3 places.

a000387.name: Rencontres numbers: number of permutations of [n] with exactly two fixed points.

a000388.name: Number of permutations of an n-sequence discordant with three given permutations (see reference) in n-2 places.

a000392.name: Stirling numbers of second kind S(n,3).

a000393.name: Number of n-node rooted trees of height 6.

a000395.name: 6th power of rooted tree enumerator; number of linear forests of 6 rooted trees.

a000396.name: Perfect numbers k: k is equal to the sum of the proper divisors of k.

a000399.name: Unsigned Stirling numbers of first kind s(n,3).

a000404.name: Numbers that are the sum of 2 nonzero squares.

a000405.name: Number of 6-level labeled rooted trees with n leaves.

a000408.name: Numbers that are the sum of three nonzero squares.

a000409.name: Singular n X n (0,1)-matrices: the number of n X n (0,1)-matrices having distinct, nonzero ordered rows, but having at least two equal columns or at least one zero column.

a000410.name: Number of singular n X n rational (0,1)-matrices.

a000412.name: Number of bipartite partitions of n white objects and 3 black ones.

a000413.name: Let A(n) = #{(i,j,k): i^2 + j^2 + k^2 <= n}, V(n) = (4/3)*Pi*n^(3/2), P(n) = A(n) - V(n); A000092 gives values of n where |P(n)| sets a new record; sequence gives A(A000092(n)).

a000414.name: Numbers that are the sum of 4 nonzero squares.

a000415.name: Numbers that are the sum of 2 but no fewer nonzero squares.

a000418.name: Number of n-node rooted trees of height 7.

a000419.name: Numbers that are the sum of 3 but no fewer nonzero squares.

a000421.name: Number of isomorphism classes of connected 3-regular (trivalent, cubic) loopless multigraphs of order 2n.

a000422.name: Concatenation of numbers from n down to 1.

a000423.name: a(n) is smallest number > a(n-1) of form a(i)*a(j), i < j < n.

a000429.name: Number of n-node rooted trees of height 8.

a000435.name: Normalized total height of all nodes in all rooted trees with n labeled nodes.

a000440.name: Number of permutations of an n-sequence discordant with three given permutations (see reference) in n-4 places.

a000444.name: Partially labeled rooted trees with n nodes (3 of which are labeled).

a000446.name: Smallest number that is the sum of 2 squares (allowing zeros) in exactly n ways.

a000449.name: Rencontres numbers: number of permutations of [n] with exactly 3 fixed points.

a000453.name: Stirling numbers of the second kind, S(n,4).

a000454.name: Unsigned Stirling numbers of first kind s(n,4).

a000459.name: Number of multiset permutations of {1, 1, 2, 2, ..., n, n} with no fixed points.

a000460.name: Eulerian numbers (Euler's triangle: column k=3 of A008292, column k=2 of A173018).

a000465.name: Number of bipartite partitions of n white objects and 4 black ones.

a000469.name: 1 together with products of 2 or more distinct primes.

a000470.name: Number of permutations of an n-sequence discordant with three given permutations (see reference) in n-5 places.

a000473.name: Number of genus 0 rooted maps with 5 faces and n vertices.

a000474.name: Number of nonisomorphic 1-factorizations of complete graph K_{2n}.

a000475.name: Rencontres numbers: number of permutations of [n] with exactly 4 fixed points.

a000476.name: Number of permutations of an n-sequence discordant with three given permutations (see reference) in n-1 places.

a000478.name: Number of ways of placing n labeled balls into 3 indistinguishable boxes with at least 2 balls in each box.

a000481.name: Stirling numbers of the second kind, S(n,5).

a000482.name: Unsigned Stirling numbers of first kind s(n,5).

a000483.name: Associated Stirling numbers: second order reciprocal Stirling numbers (Fekete) [[n, 3]]. The number of 3-orbit permutations of an n-set with at least 2 elements in each orbit.

a000485.name: Partially labeled trees with n nodes (4 of which are labeled).

a000486.name: One half of the number of permutations of [n] such that the differences have 4 runs with the same signs.

a000487.name: Number of permutations of length n with exactly two valleys.

a000489.name: Card matching: Coefficients B[n,3] of t^3 in the reduced hit polynomial A[n,n,n](t).

a000491.name: Number of bipartite partitions of n white objects and 5 black ones.

a000492.name: Number of permutations of an n-sequence discordant with three given permutations (see reference) in n-6 places.

a000497.name: S2(j,2j+2) where S2(n,k) is a 2-associated Stirling number of the second kind.

a000498.name: Eulerian numbers (Euler's triangle: column k=4 of A008292, column k=3 of A173018)

a000500.name: Number of permutations of an n-sequence discordant with three given permutations (see reference) in n-7 places.

a000502.name: Number of genus 0 rooted maps with 6 faces and n vertices.

a000504.name: S2(j,2j+3) where S2(n,k) is a 2-associated Stirling number of the second kind.

a000505.name: Eulerian numbers (Euler's triangle: column k=5 of A008292, column k=4 of A173018).

a000506.name: One half of the number of permutations of [n] such that the differences have 5 runs with the same signs.

a000507.name: Number of permutations of [n] with exactly 3 increasing runs of length at least 2.

a000514.name: Eulerian numbers (Euler's triangle: column k=6 of A008292, column k=5 of A173018)

a000517.name: Number of permutations of length n with exactly three valleys.

a000519.name: Number of equivalence classes of nonzero regular 0-1 matrices of order n.

a000521.name: Coefficients of modular function j as power series in q = e^(2 Pi i t). Another name is the elliptic modular invariant J(tau).

a000524.name: Number of rooted trees with n nodes, 2 of which are labeled.

a000525.name: Partially labeled rooted trees with n nodes (4 of which are labeled).

a000526.name: Partially labeled trees with n nodes (5 of which are labeled).

a000531.name: From area of cyclic polygon of 2n + 1 sides.

a000534.name: Numbers that are not the sum of 4 nonzero squares.

a000535.name: Card matching: coefficients B[n,2] of t^2 in the reduced hit polynomial A[n,n,n](t).

a000537.name: Sum of first n cubes; or n-th triangular number squared.

a000543.name: Number of inequivalent ways to color vertices of a cube using at most n colors.

a000544.name: Number of permutations of length n by rises.

a000545.name: Number of ways of n-coloring a dodecahedron.

a000548.name: Squares that are not the sum of 2 nonzero squares.

a000549.name: Numbers that are the sum of 2 squares but not sum of 3 nonzero squares.

a000551.name: Number of labeled rooted trees of height 2 with n nodes.

a000552.name: Number of labeled rooted trees of height 3 with n nodes.

a000553.name: Number of labeled rooted trees of height 4 with n nodes.

a000554.name: Number of labeled trees of diameter 3 with n nodes.

a000555.name: Number of labeled trees of diameter 4 with n nodes.

a000558.name: Generalized Stirling numbers of second kind.

a000559.name: Generalized Stirling numbers of second kind.

a000560.name: Number of ways of folding a strip of n labeled stamps.

a000567.name: Octagonal numbers: n*(3*n-2). Also called star numbers.

a000568.name: Number of outcomes of unlabeled n-team round-robin tournaments.

a000570.name: Number of tournaments on n nodes determined by their score vectors.
